This paper deals with information-theoretic performance limits for secure and reliable communications, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on confidentiality constraints, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of side-information in the transmitter also suggests that it may fall under the categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the potential applications of this work in wireless communications suggest that it may also fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
